                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18101031-97-off599 t18101031-97-crimeloc602"></join>. A neighbour informed me that the prisoner had taken up a pot of mine and put it on his pocket: I pursued the prisoner, he was going along Adam-street, I saw something in his left coat pocket; I took two pots out of his pocket. I sent for a constable, he searched his premises, and found five pots in his box, and an implement for melting them. This is my pot, I took it out of his pockets.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been drinking the over night, before I had these pots on me; I did not know how they came there, I was going to take them home.</p>
